<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_READ_ANY ##### -->
<para>
This grants access to read any item in the folder, corresponding
to Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Read items&rdquo; permission.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_CREATE ##### -->
<para>
This grants access to create new items (but not subfolders) in the
folder, corresponding to Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Create items&rdquo;
permission.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_EDIT_OWNED ##### -->
<para>
This grants access to edit items in the folder that you created,
corresponding to Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Edit Own&rdquo; permission.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_DELETE_OWNED ##### -->
<para>
This grants access to delete items in the folder that you created,
corresponding to Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Delete Own&rdquo; permission.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_EDIT_ANY ##### -->
<para>
This grants access to edit any item in the folder,
corresponding to Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Edit All&rdquo; permission.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_DELETE_ANY ##### -->
<para>
This grants access to delete any item in the folder,
corresponding to Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Delete All&rdquo; permission.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_CREATE_SUBFOLDER ##### -->
<para>
This grants access to create new subfolders in the
folder, corresponding to Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Create subfolders&rdquo;
permission.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_OWNER ##### -->
<para>
This makes the user an owner of the folder, corresponding to
Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Owner&rdquo; permission. Among other things,
this allows the user to edit the permissions on the folder.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_CONTACT ##### -->
<para>
This makes the user a contact person for the folder, corresponding to
Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Folder contact&rdquo; permission. This does not
actually grant any permissions per se.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_FOLDER_VISIBLE ##### -->
<para>
This grants access to see the folder and its contents, corresponding
to Outlook&rsquo;s &ldquo;Folder visible&rdquo; permission.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_EDIT_MASK ##### -->
<para>
This is a mask of the bits that control item-editing permissions. To
give the user &ldquo;Edit None&rdquo; permission, clear the bits in
this mask.
</para>



<!-- ##### MACRO E2K_PERMISSION_DELETE_MASK ##### -->
<para>
This is a mask of the bits that control item-deleting permissions. To
give the user &ldquo;Delete None&rdquo; permission, clear the bits in
this mask.
</para>



